1) Create Maven Project

2) Once Maven Project Created 
    2.a) Update POM.xml 

3) Create hibernate.cfg.xml file inside resource folder 
     in order to create xml file , right click resource folder , select file , select location of resource folder , provide name "hibernate.cfg.xml" 
     Note : name must be same hibernate.cfg.xml

4) Sometimes cfg file may give u some errors 
   in order to resolve these issues 
    click force download solution provided by IDE

5) create new(or desired database in cfg file URL property)

6) create Entity Class
7) Create Main Class

8) run program like core java application and add in cfg file mapping property 

9) Note , Focus on Hibernate ddl property which takes either create or update dependeing upon requirement
 
